title: U S  stocks higher at close of trade  Dow Jones Industrial Average up 0 22
content:
Investing com   U S  stocks were higher after the close on Thursday  as gains in the Utilities  Healthcare and Telecoms sectors led shares higher 
At the close in New York  the Dow Jones Industrial Average gained 0 22   while the S P 500 index added 0 17   and the NASDAQ Composite index gained 0 11  
The best performers of the session on the Dow Jones Industrial Average were UnitedHealth Group Incorporated  NYSE UNH   which rose 1 06  or 1 25 points to trade at 119 30 at the close  Meanwhile  Boeing Company  NYSE BA  added 1 00  or 1 41 points to end at 143 03 and The Travelers Companies Inc  NYSE TRV  was up 0 97  or 0 96 points to 100 14 in late trade 
The worst performers of the session were Chevron Corporation  NYSE CVX   which fell 0 68  or 0 69 points to trade at 101 14 at the close  Merck   Company Inc  NYSE MRK  declined 0 39  or 0 23 points to end at 58 93 and Microsoft Corporation  NASDAQ MSFT  was down 0 36  or 0 17 points to 46 44

The worst performers were Transocean Ltd  NYSE RIG  which was down 5 03  to 18 12 in late trade  Chesapeake Energy Corporation  NYSE CHK  which lost 4 21  to settle at 12 51 and Diamond Offshore Drilling Inc  NYSE DO  which was down 4 19  to 29 01 at the close

Rising stocks outnumbered declining ones on the New York Stock Exchange by 1812 to 1311 and 2 ended unchanged  on the Nasdaq Stock Exchange  1419 rose and 1399 declined  while 3 ended unchanged

Gold for August delivery was down 0 47  or 5 60 to  1181 00 a troy ounce  Elsewhere in commodities trading  Crude oil for delivery in July fell 1 33  or 0 81 to hit  60 62 a barrel  while the July Brent oil contract fell 1 16  or 0 76 to trade at  64 94 a barrel
